On October 1, 2009, President Obama released a statement expressing appreciation for the life and teachings of Mahatma Gandhi on the anniversary of his birth. He emphasized the importance of reflecting on Gandhi's message of non-violence, which continues to inspire people and political movements around the world. The President recognized Gandhi's role in transforming American society through the civil rights movement and highlighted the roots of modern America in the nonviolent social action movement for Indian independence led by Gandhi. He called for a renewal of commitment to live Gandhi's ideals and celebrate the dignity of all human beings.